":"1214","1159":"1159","1124":"1124","um 1151":"about 1151","1218":"1218","Burg Sponheim, Burgsponheim, Landkreis Bad Kreuznach, Rheinland-Pfalz, Deutschland":"Burgsponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","Sponheim, Rheinland-Pfalz Germany":"Sponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","Burgsponheim, Rhineland-Palatinate Germany":"Burgsponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Veldenz","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Fielden  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fielden","meanings":["English: from a Middle English survival of the dative plural of Old English <i>feld</i>, denoting someone who lived ‘in the fields’. The lost district name Feldon in Warwickshire may be named with this word. Perhaps also a habitational name from Feldom in Marske, North Yorkshire, recorded as <i>Feldon</i> in 1231. See   Field  ."]}]},{"name":"Mathilde","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."],"variants":[{"name":"Mechtild","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]},{"name":"Matilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]},{"name":"Mechtilde","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mathilde von Veldenz was born about 1151, in Burgsponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany as the daughter of Graf Gerlach II von Veldenz and Frau Gerlach von II Erkelenz. She married Gottfried II. von Sponheim. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1204, in her hometown, at the age of 54."},"et":{"um 1151–1204":"umbes 1151–1204","1151–1204":"1151–1204","1159–1214":"1159–1214","1149–1183":"1149–1183","1175–1218":"1175–1218","1124–1186":"1124–1186","–Female":"Surnud","1186":"1186","1175":"1175","1151":"1151","1183":"1183","nach 1175":"pärast 1175","1204":"1204","1149":"1149","UM 1150":"umbes 1150","1214":"1214","1159":"1159","1124":"1124","um 1151":"umbes 1151","1218":"1218","Burg Sponheim, Burgsponheim, Landkreis Bad Kreuznach, Rheinland-Pfalz, Deutschland":"Burgsponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Sponheim, Rheinland-Pfalz Germany":"Sponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Burgsponheim, Rhineland-Palatinate Germany":"Burgsponheim, Bad Kreuznach, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"um 1151–1204":"noin 1151–1204","1151–1204":"1151–1204","1159–1214":"1159–1214","1149–1183":"1149–1183","1175–1218":"1175–1218","1124–1186":"1124–1186","–Female":"Kuollut","1186":"1186","1175":"1175","1151":"1151","1183":"1183","nach 1175":"1175 jälkeen","1204":"1204","1149":"1149","UM 1150":"noin 1150","1214":"1214","1159":"1159","1124"